"script": "The mantis shrimp doesn't grab its prey, it punches it. In just three thousandths of a second, its club-shaped arm fires out, accelerating faster than a bullet leaving a gun. And the strike is so violent that it boils the water around it, creating a tiny exploding bubble. This means even if the shrimp misses, the shockwave alone can knock its target out cold. The punch lands with the force of a rifle round, enough to crack open a crab's shell or even shatter aquarium glass. All from a creature smaller than your hand.",
